<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-08T15:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-08T15:45:00-05:00" n="133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/88: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-08T15:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            8, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 9</hi> (<hi rend="italic">?</hi>), <hi rend="italic">12.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The President informs me that Honduras is building road and telegraph
                                line in Nicaraguan territory which has never been claimed by
                                Honduras, and that he has ordered local governor to arrest the
                                workmen, taking care that he do so in the territory undisputably
                                Nicaraguan.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>